___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

This Inquisit script implements a template to run Linguistic Acceptability Judgments (LAJ).
LAJ take advantage of techniques used in psychophysics and provide a method to make linguistic
judgments consistent and replicable.

Reference:
Bard, E. G., Robertson, D., & Sorace, A. (1996). Magnitude Estimation of Linguistic Acceptability. 
Language, 72(1), 32–68. 
https://doi.org/10.2307/416793
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
TASK DESCRIPTION	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Participants are asked to evaluate linguistic target sentences either on Likert scales (conventional) or/and by
Magnitude Estimations (ME) (psychophysics).

The sentences are presented visually.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 2 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'linguisticacceptabilityjudgments_raw*.iqdat'

build:								The specific Inquisit version used (the 'build') that was run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (winmaciosandroid)
date, time: 						date and time script was run 
subject, group: 					with the current subject/groupnumber
session:							with the current session id

blockcode, blocknum:				the name and number of the current block (built-in Inquisit variable)
trialcode, trialnum: 				the name and number of the currently recorded trial (built-in Inquisit variable)
										Note: trialnum is a built-in Inquisit variable; it counts all trials run; even those
										that do not store data to the data file such as feedback trials. Thus, trialnum 
										may not reflect the number of main trials run per block. 
									
judgmenttype:						"Likert" vs. "Magnitude Estimation"
stimulus:							contains the current stimulus (for practice lines: the relative length of the target line)
response:							the participant's response (depends on task)
log_mejudgments:					log transform of the magnitude judgment (if applicable)
latency: 							the response latency in ms


(2) Summary data file: 'linguisticacceptabilityjudgments_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)	

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EXPERIMENTAL SET-UP 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Likert Method:
* each likert trial presents a randomly selected target sentence (random selection without replacement)
with a 5 point Likert scale and the following anchors: "extremely unnatural" to "extremely natural"
	=> to change number of anchors and anchors go to TRIALS -> likert.LAJ_likert and follow further instructions
* the Likert Method runs as many trials as specified under parameters.nr_judgments (editable parameter)

Magnitude Estimation
* each magnitude estimations presents the baseline sentence and a randomly selected target sentence (random selection without replacement)
as well as a textbox to collect the judgments
* the Magnitude Estimation Method runs as many judgments as specified under parameters.nr_judgments (editable parameter)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
STIMULI
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
* the baseline sentence for Magnitude Estimations can be set under section Editable Stimuli-> item.me_baselinesentence
* the target sentences can be set under section Editable Stimuli -> item.target_sentences
	(also set parameters.nr_judgments under Editable Parameters)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
* instructions can be edited under section Editable Instructions
=> LIKERT: item.likert_instructions
=> MAGNITUDE ESTIMATIONS:
	a) item.me_instructions
	b) page.me_practice & page.me_test	

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/LikertMethod:						true = Likert Acceptability Method is run (default)
									false = Likert Acceptability Method is NOT run

/MagnitudeEstimation:				true = Magnitude Estimation Acceptability Method is run (default)
									false = Magnitude Estimation Acceptability Method is NOT run

/nr_judgments:						specifies the number of judgments to be made (default: 4)
/fontsize_stimulus:					sets the size of the stimulus in percentage of screen height (default: 5%)
/baselinelength:					the baseline line length in screen height proportion for ME practice (default: 25%)

</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/LikertMethod = true
/MagnitudeEstimation = true
/nr_judgments = 4
/fontsize_stimulus = 5%
/baselinelinelength = 25%
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE STIMULI: change editable stimuli here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: contains all target sentences
(example sentences taken from:
Jon Sprouse, J., Schütze, C.T., & Diogo Almeida, D.(2013)  cA comparison of informal and formal acceptability judgments
using a random sample from Linguistic Inquiry 2001--2010. Lingua, 134, 219-248. Table 8)
<item target_sentences>
/1 = "We proclaimed to the public John to be a hero."
/2 = "There is likely a man to appear."
/3 = "To whom did you give what?"
/4 = "I expect that everyone will visit Mary that you do."
</item>

Note: contains the baseline sentence used for Magnitude Estimations
<item ME_baselinesentence>
/1 = "Bill knows that such books John only reads at home."
</item>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/ screencolor = white
</instruct>


Note: contains the instructions for the Likert task
<item Likert_Instructions>
/1 = "Rate the following sentence on how natural it sounds"
</item>

Note: contains the instructions for the Magnitude Estimation task
<item ME_Instructions>
/1 = "Provide a numeric value above or below 100 to indicate how long or short the TARGET line is in proportion to the BASELINE line."
/2 = "Provide a numeric value above or below 100 to indicate how good or bad the TARGET sentence is in proportion to the BASELINE sentence."
</item>

<page ME_practice>
LINE LENGTH JUDGMENTS: 
^^For the following  tasks, your are given two lines: a BASELINE line and a TARGET line.
^^The BASELINE line always has the assigned value of 100. 
^^Your task is to judge the length of the TARGET line relative to the BASELINE line by assigning a number above or
below 100 that reflects the proportional difference in length.

^^^EXAMPLE:
^^If you think the TARGET line is only half as long as the BASELINE line, you would assign the value of 50
to the TARGET LINE. 
^^If you think the TARGET line is TWICE as long as the BASELINE, you would assign the value of 200 to 
the TARGET LINE.
</page>

<page ME_test>
LINGUISTIC JUDGMENTS

^^For the previous task you judged the length of a TARGET line relative to a BASELINE line. 
^^For the next tasks, you are given two sentences: a BASELINE sentence and a TARGET sentence.
^^Just like during the line estimation tasks, the BASELINE sentence always has an assigned value of 100 and
your task is to judge how good or bad the TARGET sentence is in proportion to the BASELINE sentence by
assigning a number above or below 100.

^^^Example:
^BASELINE SENTENCE: "Mary saw her in the mirror"
^TARGET SENTENCE: "The fox over the bunny jumped"

^^If you think the TARGET SENTENCE is only half as good as the BASELINE sentence, you would assign a number of 50.
^If you think the TARGET SENTENCE is about 80% as good as the BASELINE sentence, you would assign 80.
</page>

<page end>
You have reached the end of the task. Thank you for your participation!
</page>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE LISTS: change editable lists here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: contains the lengths of the practice lines for the Magnitude Estimations
relative to the predetermined baselinelength; by default 6 line lengths are run
<list practicelinelengths>
/items = (0.95, 1.05, 0.8, 1.2, 0.5, 1.5)
/replace = false
/resetinterval = 1
</list>

**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/ canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/ minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ inputdevice = mouse
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

********************
raw data
********************

<data>
/columns = (build, computer.platform, date, time, subject, group, session, 
blockcode, blocknum, trialcode, trialnum, values.judgmenttype,
values.stimulus, response, expressions.log_mejudgments, latency)
</data>

********************
summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/judgmenttype:							"Likert" vs. "Magnitude Estimation"
/stimulus:								contains the current stimulus (for practice lines: the relative length of the target line)
/count_judgments:						updates the number of judgments that have been made
/MEresponse:							stores the current magnitude estimation
/targetlinelength:						stores the current target line length in screen height percentage
											(only relevant for ME tasks)
completed:								0 = script was not completed; 1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

<values>
/judgmenttype = ""
/stimulus = ""
/count_judgments = 0
/MEresponse = 0
/targetlinelength = 0
</values>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/log_MEjudgments:  log transform of the magnitude judgment (if applicable)

<expressions>
/log_MEjudgments = if (values.MEresponse > 0) log(values.meresponse) else "NA"
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<text Likert_Instructions>
/items = Likert_Instructions
/select = 1
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, 20%)
/size = (70%, 10%)
</text>

<text ME_Instructions>
/items = ME_Instructions
/select = 2
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, text.targetsentence_me.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 10%)
/size = (70%, 10%)
</text>

<text ME_PracticeInstructions>
/items = ME_Instructions
/select = 1
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, shape.targetline.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 10%)
/size = (70%, 10%)
</text>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	STIMULI
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

Note:
* randomly selects one of the target sentences (without replacement) for the Likert Task
<text targetsentence_Likert>
/items = target_sentences
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", parameters.fontsize_stimulus, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, 30%)
</text>

<text baseline>
/items = ("BASELINE (acceptability: 100)")
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", parameters.fontsize_stimulus, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, 20%)
</text>

<text ME_baselinesentence>
/items = ME_baselinesentence
/select = 1
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", parameters.fontsize_stimulus, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/position = (50%, text.baseline.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 2%)
/ txcolor = white
/txbgcolor = black
</text>

<text target>
/items = ("TARGET:")
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", parameters.fontsize_stimulus, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, text.me_baselinesentence.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 10%)
</text>

Note:
* randomly selects one of the target sentences (without replacement) for the Magnitude Estimation Task
<text targetsentence_ME>
/items = target_sentences
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", parameters.fontsize_stimulus, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = white
/txbgcolor = black
/position = (50%, text.target.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 2%)
</text>

********************************
Practice Lines for Magnitude 
Estimations
********************************
<text practicebaseline>
/items = ("BASELINE (length: 100)")
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, 20%)
</text>

<shape baselineline>
/shape = rectangle
/size = (parameters.baselinelinelength, 1%)
/color = black
/position = (50%, 25%)
</shape>

<text practicetargetline>
/items = ("TARGET")
/select = noreplace
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/position = (50%, 35%)
</text>

<shape targetline>
/shape = rectangle
/size = (values.targetlinelength, 1%)
/color = black
/position = (50%, 40%)
</shape>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	LIKERT TRIALS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
* presents a randomly selected target sentence and 5 point Likert scale
* to change the number of scale points adjust /numpoints = 
* to change the anchors, change /anchors = 
* calls itself until the specified number of judgments has been made

<likert LAJ_likert>
/stimulusframes = [1 = targetsentence_likert, Likert_Instructions]
/numpoints = 5
/labels=("extremely unnatural", "somewhat unnatural", "possible", "somewhat natural", "extremely natural")
/position=(50%,70%)
/ontrialend = [
	values.stimulus = text.targetsentence_likert.currentItem;
	values.count_judgments += 1;
]
/branch = [return likert.laj_likert;]
</likert>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	MAGNITUDE ESTIMATION TRIALS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*************************
Practice
*************************

Notes:
* presents the baseline line and a randomly selected target line
* permits positive integers and 0 as responses

<openended practice_ME>
/ontrialbegin = [values.targetlinelength = 1% * list.practicelinelengths.nextValue * parameters.baselinelinelength]
/stimulusframes = [1 = targetline, baselineline, me_practiceinstructions, practicebaseline, practicetargetline]
/position = (50%, 75%)
/mask = positiveintegerorzero
/ monkeyresponse = ("110","105","85")
/ontrialend = [
	values.stimulus = list.practicelinelengths.currentValue;
	values.MEresponse = openended.practice_me.response;
]
/branch = [
	if (openended.practice_me.trialcount < list.practicelinelengths.itemCount) 
		return openended.practice_me;
	else return null;
]
</openended>

*************************
Test
*************************

Notes:
* presents the baseline sentence and a randomly selected target sentence
* permits positive integers and 0 as responses
* calls itself until the specified number of judgments has been made
<openended LAJ_ME>
/stimulusframes = [1 = targetsentence_me, me_baselinesentence, baseline, target, ME_Instructions]
/position = (50%, text.me_instructions.vposition + parameters.fontsize_stimulus + 3* parameters.fontsize_stimulus)
/mask = positiveintegerorzero
/ monkeyresponse = ("110","105","85")
/ontrialend = [
	values.stimulus = text.targetsentence_me.currentItem;
	values.MEresponse = openended.laj_me.response;
	values.count_judgments += 1;
]
/branch = [return openended.laj_me;]
</openended>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	BLOCKS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

Note: 
* runs the Likert Language Acceptability Judgements 
* is skipped if parameters.LikertMethod = false
* stops when the specified number of judgments has been made
<block LAJ_likert>
/skip = [parameters.LikertMethod == false]
/onblockbegin = [
	values.count_judgments = 0;
	values.judgmenttype = "Likert";
]
/trials = [1 = LAJ_likert]
/stop = [values.count_judgments == parameters.nr_judgments]
</block>

Note: 
* runs the Magnitude Estimation Acceptability Judgement Practice ("line judgments")
* is skipped if parameters.MagnitudeEstimation = false
* runs 6 practice trials
<block LAJ_practiceME>
/skip = [parameters.MagnitudeEstimation == false]
/preinstructions = (ME_practice)
/onblockbegin = [values.judgmenttype = "MagnitudeEstimation"]
/trials = [1= practice_me]
</block>

Note: 
* runs the Magnitude Estimation Acceptability Judgements 
* is skipped if parameters.MagnitudeEstimation = false
* stops when the specified number of judgments has been made
<block LAJ_ME>
/skip = [parameters.MagnitudeEstimation == false]
/preinstructions = (ME_test)
/onblockbegin = [
	values.count_judgments = 0;
	values.judgmenttype = "MagnitudeEstimation";
]
/trials = [1 = laj_me]
/stop = [values.count_judgments == parameters.nr_judgments]
</block>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPERIMENT
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<expt a>

/blocks = [
	1 = LAJ_Likert; 
	2 = LAJ_practiceME; 
	3 = LAJ_ME;
]
</expt>

